1. Download Latest NodejS - https://nodejs.org/en/.
2. To check if you have Node.js installed, run this command in your terminal:
   node -v
3. Open NodejS Command Prompt and run this command in your terminal:
   npm install npm@latest -g
4. To confirm that you have npm installed you can run this command in your terminal:
   npm -v
5. To Insall create-react-app, run this command in your terminal:
   npm install -g create-react-app
6. Now create your project folder in a directory you wish, run this command in your terminal:
   syntax : create-react-app Project name/folder name 
            create-react-app React-App  ( in this case my Project name / folder name is React-App).
7. After running the above step, you will get the project structure without any configuration.
8. After Project Setup, Run npm start to launch the development server. The browser will open
   automatically with the created appâ€™s URL. runn this command in your terminal:
   npm start
9. Copy and paste the following URL in your browser.
   http://localhost:3000/ - 